INSERT INTO `questions_titles` VALUES (1,'Incomplete Sentences - Set 1','Complete the following sentences by choosing the correct option.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 18:57:00','2025-06-08 18:57:00'),(2,'Incomplete Sentences - Set 2','Complete the following sentences by choosing the correct option.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 18:59:09','2025-06-08 18:59:09'),(3,'Error Recognition - Set 1','Identify the part of the sentence that contains an error.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:05:18','2025-06-08 19:05:18'),(4,'Error Recognition - Set 2','Identify the part of the sentence that contains an error.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:05:28','2025-06-08 19:46:21'),(5,'Company Meeting - Internal Email','Dear Team,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I would like to remind everyone that we have a mandatory company meeting scheduled for Friday, July 12th, at 10:00 AM in the main conference room.\nThe purpose of the meeting is to discuss the progress of our current projects, upcoming deadlines, and departmental goals for the next quarter. We will also take some time to acknowledge recent achievements and welcome new team members.\nPlease come prepared to share updates from your department. If you are unable to attend, inform HR as soon as possible.\n\nBest regards,\nSarah Jenkins\nOperations Manager','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:14:23','2025-06-08 19:14:23'),(6,'Local Library Expansion Project','The City Council has approved a five million dollars expansion of the downtown public library. The project aims to increase seating capacity, add a new children\'s section, and modernize digital resources. Construction is scheduled to begin in September and is expected to last about one year. In addition to expanding physical space, the library will introduce new community programs, including coding workshops for teenagers and a monthly author talk series. City officials believe the project will make the library a more dynamic space for lifelong learning. Residents are encouraged to share their suggestions during upcoming public forums.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:14:25','2025-06-08 19:14:25'),(7,'The Lost Wallet','Anna was walking through the park on her way home from work when she noticed a wallet lying on the ground. She picked it up and opened it, finding several credit cards and an ID. The wallet belonged to a man named Peter Davis. Unsure what to do, Anna decided to take the wallet to the nearest police station. On her way there, she received a phone call from Peter himself, who had tracked his wallet using an app. Grateful for Annaâ€™s honesty, Peter offered to meet her and thank her in person. They agreed to meet at a nearby cafÃ©, where Peter rewarded her with a heartfelt thank you and a small gift.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:14:26','2025-06-08 19:14:26'),(8,'Breakthrough in Renewable Energy Storage','Scientists at the European Institute of Technology have announced a groundbreaking advancement in renewable energy storage. A new type of ultra-efficient battery, developed over the past five years, can store solar and wind energy for significantly longer periods than existing technologies. This innovation addresses one of the major challenges in the field of sustainable energy: intermittency. The battery\'s high storage capacity and durability could transform how renewable energy is used and distributed globally.The research team has already partnered with several energy companies to begin large-scale production. Experts predict that this technology will accelerate the global transition toward cleaner energy sources. Public demonstrations of the battery\'s capabilities will be held at next month\'s International Energy Conference in Berlin.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:15:59','2025-06-08 19:15:59'),(9,'Weekend Plans - Email to a Friend','Hi Emma,\n\nHow are you? I hope your week has been good! I wanted to tell you about my plans for the weekend.\nOn Saturday morning, I\'m going to the farmer\'s market to buy some fresh fruit and vegetables. In the afternoon, I will meet Laura for lunch at the new Italian restaurant downtown. On Sunday, I\'m planning to go hiking in the hills. The weather should be sunny, so it will be a perfect day for a walk in nature.\nLet me know if you want to join us for lunch or hiking. It would be great to see you!\n\nTake care,\nSophie','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:16:00','2025-06-08 19:16:00'),(10,'New Library Hours and Services','Attention all library members:\n\nStarting next month, the City Public Library will introduce new opening hours to better serve the community.The library will now be open from 8:00 AM to 8:00 PM, Monday through Friday, and from 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM on Saturdays. The library will remain closed on Sundays.\nIn addition to the extended hours, the library will offer free weekend workshops on topics such as digital skills, creative writing, and local history. \nMembers are encouraged to register early for these workshops, as spaces are limited.\n\nFor more information, please visit our website or contact the library front desk.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:17:38','2025-06-08 19:17:38'),(11,'Change in Remote Work Policy','MEMO\n\nTo: All Employees  \nFrom: HR Department  \nSubject: Remote Work Policy Update\n\nDear Team,\n\nStarting from next month, employees will be allowed to work remotely up to three days per week, based on departmental needs. All managers will coordinate schedules to ensure business continuity.\nEmployees must submit their preferred remote work days by Friday of the current week. Company-provided laptops must be used when working remotely. \nPlease note that attendance at important team meetings on-site remains mandatory.\n\nIf you have any questions, contact your department manager or HR.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:23:40','2025-06-08 19:23:40'),(12,'Wireless Earbuds - Customer Review','I recently purchased the SonicSound Wireless Earbuds, and overall, I\'m very satisfied with the product. The sound quality is excellent, with clear highs and deep bass. The battery life is also impressive â€” I can use them for about 8 hours on a single charge. The only drawback is the size of the earbuds. They are a bit larger than expected and may not fit comfortably for everyone. However, for the price, these earbuds offer great value. I would definitely recommend them to anyone looking for affordable wireless audio.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:23:42','2025-06-08 19:23:42'),(13,'Welcome to Ocean View Hotel','Dear Guest,\n\nWelcome to the Ocean View Hotel! We are delighted to have you here. Our restaurant is open from 6:30 AM to 10:00 PM. Breakfast is served from 6:30 AM to 10:00 AM. Free Wi-Fi is available throughout the hotel. The fitness center is open 24 hours.\nIf you need any assistance, please call the front desk at extension 0.\nWe hope you enjoy your stay!\n\nSincerely,  \nHotel Management','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:23:43','2025-06-08 19:23:43'),(14,'Recent Trends in Renewable Energy Usage','According to the 2025 Global Energy Report, renewable energy sources accounted for 34% of the world\'s total energy production last year, up from 28% five years ago. Solar power remains the fastest-growing sector, with a 12% annual increase in capacity. Wind energy follows closely, particularly in Europe and North America. However, challenges remain. The variability of renewable sources and the need for improved energy storage solutions continue to be key issues for the industry. Experts predict that with continued investment and technological advancements, renewables could surpass 50% of global production within the next decade.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:23:44','2025-06-08 19:23:44'),(15,'Company Policy Update','Company Policy Update - Paid Time Off (PTO)\n\nEffective January 1st, all employees will receive an additional 3 days of PTO per year. This applies to both full-time and part-time staff. To request PTO, employees must submit a form via the HR portal at least two weeks in advance. PTO requests are approved on a first-come, first-served basis and subject to business needs. Unused PTO can be carried over to the following year, up to a maximum of 10 days. \n\nFor questions, please contact the HR department.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:25:51','2025-06-08 19:25:51'),(16,'Business Travel Itinerary','Business Trip Itinerary for Ms. Jane Lee\n\nDate: June 15-17\nDestination: Chicago\n\nJune 15\n09:00 - Flight UA123 to Chicago\n11:30 - Arrive at O\'Hare Airport\n12:00 - Check-in at Grand Hotel\n\nJune 16\n09:00 - Client meeting at ABC Corp.\n12:30 - Lunch with partners\n15:00 - Workshop at Convention Center\n\nJune 17\n10:00 - Visit local office\n13:00 - Flight UA456 back to New York.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:25:52','2025-06-08 19:25:52'),(17,'Job Posting: Marketing Manager','We are seeking an experienced Marketing Manager to join our dynamic team.\n\nResponsibilities:\n- Develop and execute marketing strategies.\n- Manage digital campaigns and social media.\n- Collaborate with sales and product teams.\n\nRequirements:\n- Bachelorâ€™s degree in Marketing or related field.\n- Minimum 5 years of marketing experience.\n- Strong analytical and communication skills.\n\nBenefits:\n- Competitive salary\n- Health insurance\n- Opportunities for professional growth.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:25:54','2025-06-08 19:25:54'),(18,'New High-Speed Rail Project Launched','The government has officially launched a new high-speed rail project that aims to connect major cities across the country. Construction is scheduled to begin next year and is expected to be completed by 2030. The rail system will significantly reduce travel time between major hubs, offering an eco-friendly alternative to air and road travel. Officials estimate that the project will create over 50,000 new jobs during construction and another 10,000 permanent jobs once operational.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:25:55','2025-06-08 19:25:55'),(19,'Double Passage on Workplace Communication - Set 1','Passage 1:  \nEffective workplace communication is essential for a productive environment. It includes verbal and non-verbal methods such as emails, meetings, and body language.  \nPassage 2:  \nMiscommunication can lead to mistakes and reduced morale. Companies often invest in training programs to improve communication skills among employees.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:31:26','2025-06-08 19:31:26'),(20,'Double Passage on Climate Change Effects - Set 2','Passage 1:  \nGlobal temperatures have risen steadily over the past century. This increase is linked to human activities like burning fossil fuels.  \nPassage 2:  \nRising temperatures contribute to melting ice caps, sea level rise, and more extreme weather events, threatening ecosystems and communities.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:31:26','2025-06-08 19:31:26'),(21,'Double Passage on Historical Inventions - Set 3','Passage 1:  \nThe invention of the printing press revolutionized the spread of information in the 15th century, making books more accessible.  \nPassage 2:  \nLater inventions, like the telegraph and telephone, further enhanced long-distance communication and shaped modern society.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:31:27','2025-06-08 19:31:27'),(22,'Double Passage on Healthy Living Habits - Set 4','Passage 1:  \nRegular exercise benefits both physical and mental health, reducing risks of chronic diseases.  \nPassage 2:  \nA balanced diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and whole grains supports energy levels and overall well-being.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:31:27','2025-06-08 19:31:27'),(23,'Double Passage on Online Learning Trends - Set 5','Passage 1:  \nOnline learning platforms have grown rapidly in recent years, offering a wide range of courses from programming to language learning. Flexibility is one of their key advantages.  \nPassage 2:  \nHowever, online learning requires strong self-discipline and time management skills. Without these, learners may struggle to complete courses successfully.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:43:18','2025-06-08 19:46:21'),(24,'Double Passage on Urban vs Rural Living - Set 6','Passage 1:  \nLiving in a city offers many conveniences such as public transport, entertainment, and career opportunities. However, it can also mean more noise and pollution.  \nPassage 2:  \nRural living provides peace, natural surroundings, and a slower pace of life. On the downside, access to healthcare and jobs may be more limited.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:43:18','2025-06-08 19:43:18'),(25,'Double Passage on Space Exploration - Set 7','Passage 1:  \nIn recent years, private companies have entered the space industry, launching rockets and planning missions to the Moon and Mars.  \nPassage 2:  \nSpace exploration has led to many technological innovations that benefit life on Earth, such as satellite communication and advanced materials.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:43:19','2025-06-08 19:43:19'),(26,'Double Passage on Traveling for Business - Set 8','Passage 1:  \nBusiness travel allows employees to attend meetings, conferences, and build relationships with international partners.  \nPassage 2:  \nWhile valuable, business travel can also cause fatigue and disrupt work-life balance, which is why some companies now promote virtual meetings instead.','READING',NULL,'ACTIVE','2025-06-08 19:43:20','2025-06-08 19:43:20'),(27,'Audio - At a CafÃ©','default: Listen to the following short conversation and answer the listed questions.\nperson 1: Good morning! What would you like to order?\nperson 2: Good morning. I would like a cup of coffee and a sandwich, please.\nperson 1: Sure. Would you like it to go or to have here?\nperson 2: Iâ€™ll have it here, thank you.\nperson 1: Great, Iâ€™ll bring it to your table in a moment.