INSERT INTO `recommendations` VALUES (1,1,'To further improve, the student should focus on practicing error recognition exercises, especially those that involve subtle grammatical nuances. Engaging with a variety of texts that cover similar topics but present different viewpoints or information can also help in distinguishing between passages more effectively. Additionally, reviewing advanced grammar rules and applying them in context through writing and speaking exercises will strengthen their overall language proficiency. For TOEIC preparation, timed practice tests that include a mix of question types and difficulty levels will help the student become more comfortable with the exam format and improve time management skills.','2025-06-08 20:42:35','2025-06-08 20:42:35'),(2,2,'Given the student\'s current level, it is recommended to start with foundational English language learning materials focusing on basic grammar, vocabulary, and simple reading comprehension exercises. Engaging with A2 level materials consistently will help build a solid base. Additionally, practicing with TOEIC-specific preparation books that start with beginner levels can gradually introduce the student to the format and types of questions found in the exam. It\'s also beneficial to incorporate listening practice, as the TOEIC exam includes a listening section. Seeking guidance from a language tutor or enrolling in an English language course could provide structured learning and personalized feedback. Regular practice, patience, and persistence are key to improving proficiency and confidence in English.','2025-06-08 21:22:27','2025-06-08 21:22:27'),(3,3,'To improve reading comprehension, the student should start with texts at their current level (A2) and gradually work up to more complex materials. Practicing with TOEIC-specific reading exercises can help familiarize them with the exam format. For grammar and error recognition, targeted exercises focusing on common mistakes and sentence structure are recommended. Engaging with English media, such as news articles and podcasts, can also enhance vocabulary and comprehension skills. Consistent practice with both listening and reading materials, along with feedback on errors, will be crucial for improvement.','2025-06-10 21:12:49','2025-06-10 21:12:49'),(4,4,'To improve, the student should focus on advanced grammar and vocabulary exercises, especially those that challenge their understanding of complex sentence structures and idiomatic expressions. Practicing with C1 and C2 level materials will be beneficial. They should also work on their listening skills by engaging with a variety of English accents and speeds, and by summarizing spoken passages to ensure comprehension. For reading comprehension, they should practice identifying key details and inferring information not explicitly stated. Regular practice with TOEIC-style questions at all levels will help familiarize them with the exam format and timing.','2025-06-12 14:43:27','2025-06-12 14:43:27'),(5,5,'To improve, the student should focus on practicing with more C1 level materials to enhance their ability to understand and infer information from complex texts. They should also work on paying closer attention to details in simpler texts to avoid missing key information. Engaging in extensive reading and listening exercises across a range of topics and difficulty levels will help broaden their comprehension skills. Additionally, practicing with TOEIC-specific materials can familiarize them with the exam format and question types, further improving their performance.','2025-06-12 16:29:22','2025-06-12 16:29:22'),(6,6,'To further improve, the student should focus on mastering advanced grammatical structures and expanding their vocabulary, especially for C1 and C2 level questions. Practicing with TOEIC-specific materials that target these higher levels can be beneficial. Additionally, the student should work on time management and double-checking answers to avoid simple mistakes in lower-level questions. Engaging in regular listening practice with a variety of English accents and speeds, as well as reading diverse texts, will help solidify their comprehension skills across all levels.','2025-06-14 22:36:47','2025-06-14 22:36:47'),(7,7,'To improve inference skills, the student should practice reading between the lines in texts and listening materials. Engaging with more complex reading passages and summarizing the main ideas and implied messages could be beneficial.','2025-06-15 00:11:06','2025-06-15 00:11:06'),(8,7,'For grammatical accuracy, focusing on verb tenses and conditional sentences through targeted exercises and practice tests would help. Utilizing grammar workbooks or online resources specifically designed for TOEIC preparation could provide the necessary practice.','2025-06-15 00:11:06','2025-06-15 00:11:06'),(9,8,'Practicar la comprensiÃ³n de lectura con textos de nivel A1 y A2, enfocÃ¡ndose en identificar informaciÃ³n especÃ­fica como fechas, lugares y acciones.','2025-06-15 00:18:55','2025-06-15 00:18:55'),(10,8,'Mejorar la comprensiÃ³n auditiva escuchando conversaciones y anuncios simples, prestando atenciÃ³n a detalles clave.','2025-06-15 00:18:55','2025-06-15 00:18:55'),(11,8,'Trabajar en el vocabulario bÃ¡sico y en la estructura de oraciones para mejorar en la secciÃ³n de completar oraciones.','2025-06-15 00:18:55','2025-06-15 00:18:55'),(12,8,'Utilizar recursos en lÃ­nea como \'British Council LearnEnglish\' para practicar habilidades bÃ¡sicas de inglÃ©s. Visita: https://learnenglish.britishcouncil.org/','2025-06-15 00:18:55','2025-06-15 00:18:55'),(13,8,'Realizar ejercicios de escucha activa, como escuchar anuncios pÃºblicos o conversaciones cortas, y luego intentar responder preguntas sobre ellos.','2025-06-15 00:18:55','2025-06-15 00:18:55'),(14,8,'Practicar la identificaciÃ³n de informaciÃ³n clave en textos cortos, subrayando fechas, nombres y acciones importantes.','2025-06-15 00:18:55','2025-06-15 00:18:55'),(15,9,'Practicar la lectura de textos tÃ©cnicos y noticias para mejorar la comprensiÃ³n de vocabulario especÃ­fico y la capacidad de inferencia. Sitios como BBC Learning English ofrecen materiales Ãºtiles.','2025-06-15 00:28:19','2025-06-15 00:28:19'),(16,9,'Realizar ejercicios de gramÃ¡tica enfocados en tiempos verbales y estructuras de oraciones complejas. Un recurso recomendado es el canal de YouTube \'English Addict with Mr Steve\'.','2025-06-15 00:28:19','2025-06-15 00:28:19'),(17,9,'Escuchar activamente conversaciones y anuncios en inglÃ©s, prestando atenciÃ³n a nÃºmeros, fechas, y condiciones. La app \'ELLLO\' ofrece ejercicios de listening gratuitos.','2025-06-15 00:28:19','2025-06-15 00:28:19'),(18,9,'Participar en simulacros de examen TOEIC completos para familiarizarse con el formato y mejorar la gestiÃ³n del tiempo. Un buen recurso es el sitio web \'Exam English\'.','2025-06-15 00:28:19','2025-06-15 00:28:19'),(19,10,'Practicar la memorizaciÃ³n de datos numÃ©ricos y porcentajes, ya que son comunes en preguntas sobre informes y estadÃ­sticas. Un ejercicio Ãºtil podrÃ­a ser crear resÃºmenes de artÃ­culos con nÃºmeros clave.','2025-06-15 00:35:45','2025-06-15 00:35:45'),(20,10,'Mejorar la atenciÃ³n a los detalles en textos informativos, como horarios y procedimientos. Se recomienda subrayar o tomar notas de fechas, horas y pasos a seguir mientras se lee.','2025-06-15 00:35:45','2025-06-15 00:35:45'),(21,10,'Reforzar el conocimiento de estructuras gramaticales, especialmente condicionales y el uso de adverbios de frecuencia. Realizar ejercicios especÃ­ficos sobre estos temas puede ser muy beneficioso.','2025-06-15 00:35:45','2025-06-15 00:35:45'),(22,10,'Desarrollar estrategias para identificar el tono y la intenciÃ³n en anuncios y conversaciones. Escuchar una variedad de anuncios pÃºblicos y practicar identificando el tono puede ayudar.','2025-06-15 00:35:45','2025-06-15 00:35:45'),(23,10,'Para mejorar en la secciÃ³n de LISTENING, se recomienda practicar con materiales autÃ©nticos, como anuncios de aeropuertos y conversaciones de negocios. Un buen recurso es el canal de YouTube \'TOEIC Listening Practice\', que ofrece ejercicios similares a los del examen.','2025-06-15 00:35:45','2025-06-15 00:35:45');
